The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The focus on pairwise compatibility graphs suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as the most likely category. The paper also deals with intersection graphs, which are often studied in cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of weighted trees and real numbers suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible category. The study of graph classes and their properties suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as other possible categories.
